SIMPLE: forswear
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forswear
<hw>For*swear"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Forswore</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Forsworn</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Forswearing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>forsweren</ets>, <ets>forswerien</ets>, AS. <ets>forswerian</ets>;
pref. <ets>for-</ets> + <ets>swerian</ets> to swear. See <er>For-</er>,
and <er>Swear</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To reject
or renounce upon oath; hence, to renounce earnestly, determinedly, or
with protestations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I . . . do <qex>forswear</qex> her.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deny upon oath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like innocence, and as serenely bold⟦br⟧
As truth, how loudly he <qex>forswears</qex> thy gold!</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To forswear one's self</b></col>, <cd>to swear falsely;
to perjure one's self.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Thou shalt not <xex>forswear
thyself</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Matt. v. 33.</au></rj></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Perjure</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forswear</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Forswear
<hw>For*swear"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To swear falsely; to commit
perjury.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forswearer</ent>⟦br⟧
